<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0002204> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBPROP_0000003> "There are more than 50,000 extant vertebrate species, representing over 500 million years of evolution. During that time, the vertebrate musculoskeletal systems have adapted to aquatic, terrestrial, fossorial, and arboreal lifestyles, while simultaneously retaining functionally integrated axial and appendicular skeletal systems.[well established][VHOG]" <https://purl.wholepersonphysiome.org/wpp/muscular-system> .
